 {"id":"frankenpandas-70d1","title":"fd90.17: schema-aware table_exists_in_schema","description":"fd90 sub-bead: schema-aware table_exists. Currently SqlConnection::table_exists takes only the table name; on multi-schema backends the same name can exist in different schemas. Add table_exists_in_schema(&self, table, schema) trait method with default impl that delegates to table_exists (ignores schema). rusqlite override matches default since SQLite has one namespace per connection. write_sql_with_options Fail branch routes through table_exists_in_schema with options.schema so SQLite users see no behavior change but multi-schema backends correctly check the targeted schema. 4 tests covering default delegation, multi-schema stub override, write_sql Fail with schema=Some on SQLite (still bare check), reject pre-existing.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:52:17.172374069Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:55:03.995352820Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T19:55:03.991963883Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fd90","review","schema","sql"]}
