 {"id":"frankenpandas-7135r","title":"fd90.107: README df.transform("zscore") wouldn't compile — DataFrame::transform takes closure, not string","description":"fd90.74-106 README audit. Line 649 in 'Multiple ways to apply custom logic' shows:

  let normed = df.transform("zscore")?;

But crates/fp-frame/src/lib.rs:19590 declares:
  pub fn transform<F>(&self, func: F) -> Result<Self, FrameError>
  where F: Fn(&Scalar) -> Scalar

DataFrame::transform takes a closure, NOT a string. Passing "zscore" wouldn't compile. The string-based transform(func_name: &str) ONLY exists on DataFrameGroupBy (per the doc-comment 'Matches df.groupby(col).transform(func_name) semantics'). All surrounding examples in the same code block (applymap, apply_row, assign_fn, pipe) correctly use closures.

Fix: rewrite the example to use a closure returning a Scalar of the same dtype, matching the actual signature. Or replace with the GroupBy variant if showing a string-based transform makes more sense in that paragraph. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T10:28:47.793804683Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T10:30:27.577119248Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T10:30:27.574272310Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
